Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 18:13:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] Emit in-app notifications on social actions and
 achievement unlocks

Adds reusable create_notification() and get_actor_display_name() helpers
to the notifications router (co-located with the Notification model),
then wires them into the core action paths so the notifications feed
actually populates:

- Comment on a post -> notifies the post author
- React to a post   -> notifies the post author (new reactions only)
- Follow a user     -> notifies the followed user
- Achievement unlock -> notifies the earner (after batch commit)

All notification creation is non-fatal (wrapped, self-notifications
skipped) so it can never break the underlying action. Achievement
notifications are collected during the check loop and emitted after the
batch commit to preserve transaction semantics.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01Q1rk7BZrjN1to3WbJRAPyR
